(NOTE: Any Facts in this speech are from 2013 and some may only apply in New Zealand, like the money value. Not Everything in this speech is a fact, but some are just my opinion. And If you loveÂ COD, im sorry, but I just needed to compare MC To something Gory and Expensive [This Speech was meant to be for school, so thats why I say that MC is good because its not R16 or R18])       DoÂ you want to play a game thats Fun? A game where you can Kill peopleÂ with Machine Guns and cut people in half? Well then this is the WrongÂ Game for you. Minecraft is not a game thats all about Killing andÂ Good graphics, its a game of Creativity, Skill and Quick Reactions.Â Minecraft has over 4 Million people playing it and it is a game thatÂ when you play for 2 hours, you love it. Minecraft is cheaper thanÂ most popular games, has good gameplay and its violence isn't as goryÂ as most modern games today.     Have youÂ always wanted to get a really good game but it was worth One-HundredÂ dollars or more? Well this is not a game worth One-Hundred dollarsÂ that you can't get, it's actually just Thirty-Two dollars NewÂ Zealand, and lots of people play it. For example, the new Call ofÂ Duty Ghosts game has come out at One-Hundred and thirty-two dollarsÂ NewZealand! That's a lot for 1 game, when with that money you couldÂ buy 1 Minecraft account and still have One-Hundred dollars left toÂ buy anything you want, therefore you could buy almost 4 moreÂ Minecraft accounts in total. What game would you rather buy with yourÂ money?     Are you aÂ fan of old games, do you care about the graphics, or do you careÂ about the good gameplay and storyline? Minecraft is a PixilatedÂ Sandbox game, which means that its a game with no real ending, orÂ path. In Minecraft, you choose your path and destiny. You could BuildÂ whatever you want, live however you want, play with whoever you wantÂ and play whenever you want! As Minecraft might be a fun game to play,Â it can also be used for education. For example, in Social Science myÂ class and I needed to build a model castle, but I didn't use wood orÂ cardboard, I built it in Minecraft. Easy to build and very portable.Â Minecraft also has countless crafting recipes, which can improve yourÂ Memory, and even has a mode to turn Monsters offÂ for any young children.     Lastly,Â Do you ever say â€œWow! Look at that awesome game! Mum, can I getÂ it?â€ and then you realize its R16 or R18 and your mum refuses?Â Minecraft is not R16 or R18, it doesn't even have a rating, becauseÂ the game hasn't officially come out yet, and still has developmentÂ versions. A survey was put on a website with different Ratings thatÂ Minecraft would be. The highest out of Seven choices at 40% was AgesÂ 10+. On Another Website, someone asked what the Rating for MinecraftÂ was and most comments was M, for Cartoon Violence and Mild LanguageÂ from online players and 10+, for just Cartoon Violence with no blood.Â So you're Legally allowed to play Minecraft for anyone under 16 or 18Â years old, but not for Call of Duty.     InÂ Conclusion, Minecraft is a Great Game to play by yourself or withÂ friends. Its on most devices; Mac, PC Windows, Iphone and Ipad, XboxÂ 360, and Similar Versions on the Playstation 4, Playstation 3, XboxÂ One and PSP. Its Cheaper than most Popular New games, has goodÂ gameplay and is less Violent than most modern games. So what game isÂ right for you to play? Call of Duty or Minecraft?
